ile_Attributes","documentation":{"description":"Create manually a File_Attributes.\n\nThis function is for internal gnatcoll usage (used by GNATCOLL.OS.Dir).\nSee File_Attributes private declaration for parameter meanings","parameters":[{"name":"Exists","description":""},{"name":"Writable","description":""},{"name":"Readable","description":""},{"name":"Executable","description":""},{"name":"Symbolic_Link","description":""},{"name":"Regular","description":""},{"name":"Directory","description":""},{"name":"Stamp","description":""},{"name":"Length","description":""}]}},{"id":"2f5773bda7994a8e","name":"Stat","qualified_name":"GNATCOLL.OS.Stat.Stat","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/gnatcoll_26.0.0_cc5dd0a1/7ccbed38d8b88fe1ce3c718d0f0a1da149c4b5af155bbe12ed9d190dcda52463/core/src/os/gnatcoll-os-stat.ads","line":39,"column":13},"code":"function Stat\n   (Path            : UTF8.UTF_8_String;\n    Follow_Symlinks : Boolean := True)\n   return File_Attributes","documentation":{"description":"Retrieve file information about a file located at Path. If\nFollow_Symlinks is True then in case the file is a symlink the\nreturned information is regarding the file which is the target of\nthe symlink. If False, return the information about the symlink itself.\n\nWhen passing a relative path, stat does not check that intermediate\ndirectories do exist. For example if file file.txt exists then stat\nreturns success when calling Stat(\"non_existing_dir/../file.txt\").\n\nIn case Path is not a valid UTF-8 string the function behaves as if the\nfile does not exist.","parameters":[{"name":"Path","description":""},{"name":"Follow_Symlinks","description":""}]}}]}